Author: Tara Nath Subedi <Tara.Subedi@windriver.com>
Date:   Wed Apr 29 16:42:06 2026 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] phc2sys: skip system clock sync when UTC offset is not valid and traceable

phc2sys: skip system clock sync when UTC offset is not valid and traceable

When a PTP grandmaster reports currentUtcOffsetValid=0 or
timeTraceable=0 in the Time Properties Data Set, the advertised
currentUtcOffset may not be reliable. Applying an incorrect UTC
offset to the system clock (CLOCK_REALTIME) can cause large time
jumps (e.g., 37 seconds for the current TAI-UTC offset).

Use the existing utc_offset_traceable check (currentUtcOffsetValid
AND timeTraceable) to gate system clock synchronization in both
do_loop and do_pps_loop. This is consistent with how clock_handle_leap
in phc2sys and clock_utc_correct in ptp4l already guard the kernel
TAI offset update. PHC-to-PHC synchronization is unaffected.

Changes in phc2sys.c:
- do_pps_loop: skip update_clock when utc_offset_traceable is false
- do_loop: skip CLOCK_REALTIME update when utc_offset_traceable is false

TEST PLAN:
PASS: Setup PTP4L with currentUtcOffsetValid=0, timeTraceable=0
PASS: Check do_loop code-path (without -d pps_device)
      /usr/sbin/phc2sys -f /etc/linuxptp/ptpinstance/phc2sys-phcinst0.conf
      -s enp81s0f2 -z /var/run/ptp4l-ptpinstc01 -w -m -l 7
      debug message: phcinst0 skipping system clock sync: UTC offset is not valid or traceable
PASS: Check do_pps_loop code-path (with -d pps_device)
      /usr/sbin/phc2sys -f /etc/linuxptp/ptpinstance/phc2sys-phcinst0.conf
      -d /dev/pps0 -s enp81s0f2 -z /var/run/ptp4l-ptpinstc01 -w -m -l 7
      debug message: phcinst0 skipping system clock sync: UTC offset is not valid or traceable
PASS: Setup PTP4L with currentUtcOffsetValid=1, timeTraceable=1
      Both above with and without pps_device, no more shows debug message
      Phc2sys starts syncing system-clock.

Signed-off-by: Tara Nath Subedi <tara.subedi@windriver.com>
---
 phc2sys.c | 15 +++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 15 insertions(+)

diff --git a/phc2sys.c b/phc2sys.c
index fe19ef5..9494655 100644
--- a/phc2sys.c
+++ b/phc2sys.c
@@ -1034,6 +1034,12 @@ static int do_pps_loop(struct phc2sys_private *priv, struct clock *clock,
 
 		if (pmc_agent_update(node) < 0)
 			continue;
+		/* don't sync system clock when UTC offset is not valid and traceable */
+		if (!pmc_agent_utc_offset_traceable(node)) {
+			pr_debug("skipping system clock sync: "
+				 "UTC offset is not valid or traceable");
+			continue;
+		}
 		update_clock(priv, clock, pps_offset, pps_ts, -1);
 	}
 	close(fd);
@@ -1706,6 +1712,15 @@ static int do_loop(struct phc2sys_private *priv, struct config *cfg, int subscri
 			    !strcmp(clock->device, priv->master->device))
 				continue;
 
+			/* don't sync system clock when UTC offset is not valid and traceable */
+			if (clock->clkid == CLOCK_REALTIME &&
+			    priv->master->node &&
+			    !pmc_agent_utc_offset_traceable(priv->master->node)) {
+				pr_debug("skipping system clock sync: "
+					 "UTC offset is not valid or traceable");
+				continue;
+			}
+
 			if (!clock->servo) {
 				pr_err("cannot update clock without servo");
 				return -1;
